hazel r oleary  wikipedia hazel r oleary from wikipedia the free encyclopedia jump to navigation search hazel oleary th united states secretary of energy in office january   – january   president bill clinton preceded by james watkins succeeded by federico peña personal details born hazel reid  may   age  newport news virginia us political party democratic spouses carl rollins divorced max robinson divorced john oleary – children  education fisk university ba rutgers university newark llb hazel reid oleary born may   was the seventh united states secretary of energy from  to  appointed by president bill clinton as of  she is the first and only woman and first and only african american to hold the position she served as president of fisk university a historically black college hbcu from  to  contents  early life and education  career  secretary of energy  fisk university  other affiliations  marriage and family  references  further reading  external links early life and educationedit hazel reid was born in newport news virginia hazels parents dr russel e reid and dr hazel reid were both physicians they when she was  months old her father and stepmother mattie a teacher raised hazel and her older sister edna reid both of the parents were successful medical doctors around the s and her stepmother was a teacher hazel attended school in a segregated school system in newport news for eight years hazel and her sister were then sent to live with an aunt in essex county new jersey and attend arts hight school an integrated school she earned a bachelors degree at fisk university in nashville in  she then married carl rollins and had a son before returning to school and earning her bachelor of laws degree from rutgers school of law in  careeredit oleary worked as a prosecutor in new jersey prosecuting organized crime cases next she became an assistant attorney general oleary got a divorce and in  moved to washington dc where she joined the consultingaccounting firm of coopers  lybrand during the carter administration oleary was appointed assistant administrator of the federal energy administration general counsel of the community services administration and administrator of the economic regulatory administration at the newly created department of energy at the department of energy hazel met her third husband jack oleary in  oleary and her husband established the consulting firm of oleary  associates in morristown new jersey where she served as vice president and general counsel after jack died of cancer hazel moved to minnesota from  to  she worked as an executive vice president of the northern states power company a minnesota based public utilities company which served approximately  million customers secretary of energyedit left to right secretary of energy hazel r oleary john s foster president william clinton and mrs john foster in  then presidentelect bill clinton announced he would nominate oleary as secretary of energy clinton officially made the nomination on january   and the senate confirmed oleary by unanimous consent the next day oleary became the first woman to serve as secretary of energy at the time she led the department of energy the department had an annual budget of  million in this position oleary won plaudits for declassifying cold warera records which showed the us government had used american citizens as guinea pigs in human radiation experiments as had long been rumored president clinton issued executive order  which created the advisory committee on human radiation experiments achre to prevent such abuses of power oleary also pushed to end nuclear testing in the united states she announced a zero tolerance policy prohibiting retaliation against whistle blowers at nuclear plants during olearys service she was criticized in a government accountability office audit of traveling too frequently and spending too much on accommodations she apologized to congressional committees in  for spending which exceeded limits on the funds appropriated to the agency for travel and resigned in january  in  johnny chung a democratic political donor claimed that oleary met with chinese oil officials after he gave  to olearys favorite charity africare in  fbi director louis freeh urged an independent investigation attorney general janet reno determined there was no evidence of wrongdoing by oleary some observes including a lawyer for the government accountability project saw some fault in olearys conduct but also saw racism and sexism in the manner in way oleary was treated fisk universityedit in  oleary was selected as president of her undergraduate alma mater fisk university a historically black college in nashville tennessee as president oleary has helped the university recapture its place in competing for top students and financial support and has attracted outstanding faculty while she accomplished major fundraising the university continued to struggle to build its endowment oleary speaks on september   at the minorities in energy initiative launch one way oleary tried to help the school improve its finances was through the sale of a portion of the universitys alfred stieglitz collection the collection was bequeathed to fisk by his widow and fellow artist georgia okeeffe on the condition that it never be sold fisk received proposal from a museum in arkansas to purchase a halfshare fisk appealed to the chancery court to be released from the condition prohibiting sale the court directed the state attorney general to develop an alternative plan to keep the collection in nashville and the state in september  attorney general bob d cooper proposed the collection be transferred to the tennessee arts commission and housed at the frist center for the visual arts in nashville it would be identified as the alfred stieglitz collection at fisk university the proposal is a joint state city and museum projectdead link in  she announced that she would retire at the end of the calendar year she was succeeded at fisk by h james williams other affiliationsedit olear serves as a director for alchemix corp and camac international corporation she also serves on the board of directors for nonprofit organizations such as nashville alliance for public education nashville business community for the arts and arms control association as well as a trustee on boards of the world wildlife fund morehouse college and the andrew young center of international development marriage and familyedit reid married carl g rollins jr with whom she had a son also named carl they later divorced her second marriage to abc news anchorman max robinson did not last long in  she met john f oleary then deputy secretary of energy the pair married on april  citation needed and remained married until his death from cancer referencesedit  a b executive profile hazel oleary bloomberg retrieved june     a b c d e f g h harringon linda m may   no pie in the sky tribunedigitalchicagotribune retrieved    a b c d e f g smith jessie carney  notable black american women vnr ag isbn    finkelman paul ed  encyclopedia of african american history volume  oxford oxford university press p    a b c d e f henneberger melinda november   exofficial now looks to church for solace the new york times issn  retrieved june     a b stych ed december   energy secretary candidate has experience as regulator executive wwwquestiacom the journal record retrieved    scott matthew s march  the new powers that be the clinton challenge vol  issue  wwwquestiacom black enterprise retrieved june     ifill gwen december   the transition clinton chooses  and delpores idea of cabinet quotas the new york times issn  retrieved july     pn  nomination of hazel rollins oleary for department of energy rd congress  wwwcongressgov january   retrieved june     a b letzter rafi december   here are the qualifications of all  people who served as secretary of energy before rick perry business insider retrieved june     black clout in the clinton adminis