re than  employees who enforced price controls on numerous forms of energy at this time she successfully lobbied congress to pass the fuel use act which decreased the demand for natural gas and developed conservation programs that assisted lowincome residents while working for the carter administration reid met her future husband john f o’leary who was at the time the nation’s deputy energy secretary the two married in  and together left the department to establish and manage their own energyconsulting firm o’leary associates in  following the death of her husband hazel o’leary went to work for northern state power company a minnesota utility as executive vice president for environmental and public affairs and then president of its natural gas division  in  presidentelect bill clinton announced that he would nominate o’leary to be secretary of the us department of energy she would become the second woman and third african american nominated to the clinton cabinet on january   hazel rollins reid o’leary became the seventh us secretary of energy she would direct the  employees of the agency and be the principal architect of the clinton energy policy which emphasized both conservation and innovation while in office o’leary led the effort to find safer ways to dispose of atomic waste  she gained congressional approval to convert one of three national nuclear weapons design laboratories into a research facility to study technologically advanced environmental cleanup practices  o’leary also opposed increases in energy taxes since  hazel o’leary has served as president of fisk university her alma mater  she remains an avid supporter of environmentalism she works with a variety of nonprofit organizations including the world wildlife fund morehouse college and the andrew young center of international development sourcesunited states congress senate committee of energy and natural resource hazel r o’leary nomination hearing before the committee on energy and natural resources unites states senate one hundred third congress first session on the nomination of hazel r o’leary to be secretary department of energy january  washington us gpo supt of docs congressional sales office  mary anne borrelli the president’s cabinet gender power and representation boulder colorado l rienner publishers  httpwwwdomcom contributor espiritu allison university of washington entry categories th century attorneys government appointed government federal people washington dc women copyright   blackpastorg v  blackpastblackpastorg  your donations help us to grow  we welcome your suggestions  mission statement blackpastorg is an independent nonprofit corporation c it has no affiliation with the university of washington blackpastorg is supported in part by a grant from humanities washington a statewide nonprofit organization supported by the national endowment for the humanities the state of washington and contributions from individuals and foundations african american history  the black past remembered and reclaimed an online reference guide to african american history home main featuresaah index page aaw index page gah index page perspective articles black history month blackpastorg the united states blackpastorg and the world digital archives genealogy black national anthem barack obama page  african american firsts major black office holders lgbtq page users guide site map special featuresblacks and the lds church the mentoring page preserving king county’s african american history african american ambassadors speakers bureau african and west indian capital cities dever memorial page on afrobritons historic african american churches african american ambassadors blackpast blog roll robert fikes corner blackpastorg in the classroom blackpastorg by the numbers af am historical landmarks civil war memorial page historically black colleges and universities link exchange whats new about usawards and distinctions mission statement faq blackpast video board of direct